            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Mr. I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Rev<hi rend="underline">d</hi> Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">The enclosed letter<lb/> to <persName>Mr. Cromlien</persName>,
                contains the sad <sic>inteligence</sic> of the<lb/> death of <persName>Mr. R.
                    Mayer</persName> &amp; daughter, relatives of the<lb/> above named Lady, you
                will dear sir confer a favor<lb/> by having it conveyed to her forthwith, two
                reasons<lb/> have prompted us to this liberty, first being unacquainted<lb/> with
                the proper direction and secondly the unpleasant<lb/> tidings could not we think be
                broached by any one<lb/> better calculated to do so than yourselfâ€”with
                sentiments<lb/> of regard and esteem I am Revd Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your Obedt Servt</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">L. Nathans</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Savannah</placeName>
                <date>Sept 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date>
            </p>
